'''调节T细胞'''（'''regulatory T cell'''，T<sub>reg</sub>）：是一群具有负调节机体免疫反应的[[淋巴细胞|淋巴细胞]]，通常起着维持自身耐受和避免免疫反应过度损伤机体的重要作用，但也参与肿瘤细胞逃避机体[[免疫监视|免疫监视]]和慢性感染。

70年代曾命名为抑制T细胞（suppressor T cell），因缺乏明确的表面标志，研究长期处于尴尬和停顿的境地；直到90年代研究出现转机并成为目前研究热点，但现多称为调节T细胞（regulatory T cell）。

調節性T細胞最重要的分子標記是一種轉錄因子Foxp3，在所有調節性T細胞中均可發現有多量表現。

==亚群==
调节T细胞是免疫系统的重要组成成分，可抑制其他免疫细胞的免疫反應。这是免疫系统之中重要的“自检”组分，可防止产生过激的免疫反應。调节T细胞有多种形式，但被了解的最透彻的是表达CD4、CD25及FOXP3调节T细胞（CD4+CD25+调节T细胞）。调节T细胞与[[辅助T细胞|辅助T细胞]]不同<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Hori S, Nomura T, Sakaguchi S | title = Control of regulatory T cell development by the transcription factor Foxp3 | journal = Science | volume = 299 | issue = 5609 | pages = 1057–61 | date = February 2003 | pmid = 12522256 | doi = 10.1126/science.1079490 | bibcode = 2003Sci...299.1057H | url = https://semanticscholar.org/paper/7f710d825a4b25a36f0fdef742b583c1f3da108c }}</ref>。另一类调节T细胞亚群是[[Treg17细胞|Treg17细胞]]<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Singh B, Schwartz JA, Sandrock C, Bellemore SM, Nikoopour E | title = Modulation of autoimmune diseases by interleukin (IL)-17 producing regulatory T helper (Th17) cells | journal = The Indian Journal of Medical Research | volume = 138 | issue = 5 | pages = 591–4 | date = November 2013 | pmid = 24434314 | pmc = 3928692 }}</ref>。调节T细胞参与到成功清除入侵生物后关闭免疫反應之中，同时也防止产生自身免疫反應<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Shevach EM | title = Regulatory T cells in autoimmmunity* | journal = Annual Review of Immunology | volume = 18 | issue =  | pages = 423–49 | year = 2000 | pmid = 10837065 | doi = 10.1146/annurev.immunol.18.1.423 | url = https://semanticscholar.org/paper/0859b22ec3d4493b9fd088a493c560876f2084ed }}</ref>。

CD4+ Foxp3+ CD25(high) regulatory T cells have been called "naturally occurring" regulatory T cells<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Schmetterer |first1=Klaus G. |last2=Neunkirchner |first2=Alina |last3=Pickl |first3=Winfried F. |title=Naturally occurring regulatory T cells: markers, mechanisms, and manipulation |journal=The FASEB Journal |date=June 2012 |volume=26 |issue=6 |pages=2253–2276 |doi=10.1096/fj.11-193672 |pmid=22362896 |issn=0892-6638}}</ref> to distinguish them from "suppressor" T cell populations that are generated in vitro. Additional regulatory T cell populations include [[Type_1_regulatory_T_cells_(Tr1_cells)|Tr1]], Th3, CD8+CD28-, and Qa-1 restricted T cells. The contribution of these populations to self-tolerance and immune homeostasis is less well defined. Foxp3 can be used as a good marker for mouse CD4+CD25+ T cells, although recent studies have also shown evidence for Foxp3 expression in CD4+CD25- T cells. In humans, Foxp3 is also expressed by recently activated conventional T-cells and thus does not specifically identify human Tregs.<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Sakaguchi S | title = Naturally arising CD4+ regulatory t cells for immunologic self-tolerance and negative control of immune responses | journal = Annual Review of Immunology | volume = 22 | issue =  | pages = 531–62 | year = 2004 | pmid = 15032588 | doi = 10.1146/annurev.immunol.21.120601.141122 }}</ref>


调节/抑制T细胞有很多种，可分為自然存在與誘導產生兩類：

自然存在：
* [[CD4+CD25+T细胞|CD4<sup>+</sup> CD25<sup>+</sup>T细胞]]：在维持机体对自身抗原的耐受中扮演重要角色，是目前研究最广泛深入的一种调节/抑制T细胞。

誘導產生：
* [[TR1细胞|T<sub>R</sub>1细胞]]：以分泌[[IL-10|IL-10]]为特征，负调节免疫应答。
* [[TH3细胞|T<sub>H</sub>3细胞]]：最早在口服免疫耐受性[[動物模型|動物模型]]中發現，以分泌[[轉化生長因子-β|轉化生長因子-β]]（TGF-β）作為其功能性[[細胞激素|細胞激素]]。研究顯示可能與口服免疫耐受性、黏膜免疫機制有關。

